                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3pg1j508/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>The other morning <persName>Selina</persName> &amp; myself<lb/> were bathing were\n                were not looking<lb/> at the breakers &amp; before we could<lb/> do anything down we\n                went flat.<lb/> I was dreadfully frightened I<lb/> tried to\n                    <sic>calck</sic><add>?</add> me but could<lb/> not at last a swell came\n                &amp;<lb/> that brought me to the top<lb/> I swallowed a pint of<lb/> salt water.\n                All my friends<lb/> tell me they think I am look<lb/>ing a great deal better when\n                I<lb/> was here a day or two I weighed 86 &amp; this morning I weighed<lb/> 88—you\n                can judge for your<lb/>self when we meet which I<lb/> hope will be soon you\n                better<lb/> think of coming down it would<lb/> be a great benefit to you to<lb/>\n                smell some fresh pure<lb/> salt air. I must now bid you<lb/> good bye as ma wants to\n                write</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3pg1j508/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
